Indian Equity Movers: JSW Steel, Reliance Capital, Tree House

-- B y   S h i k h a r   B a l w a n i   a n d   H e m a l   S a v a i
-- 
2011-08-26T11:03:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/indian-equity-movers-coal-india-ks-oils-mphasis-tree-house.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Mumbai trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3:30 p.m. close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
lost 297.5 points, or 1.8 percent, to 15,848.83. The BSE200
Index sank 2.1 percent to 1,964.28.  GVK Power & Infrastructure Ltd. (GVKP)  , an Indian
builder of airports and utilities, declined 3.6 percent to 16
rupees, its lowest since Nov. 2008, on concern its debt will
increase after a newspaper reported the company will buy Hancock
Prospecting Pty coal mines in  Australia .  JSW Steel Ltd. (JSTL)  ,  India ’s third-biggest producer,
tumbled 5.8 percent to 609.15 rupees, its lowest in more than
two years. India’s top court ordered a ban on mining iron ore in
Tumkur and Chitradurga districts of the southern state of
Karnataka, according to an interim order passed by a three-judge
panel headed by Chief Justice S.H. Kapadia today. NMDC fell 4.1
percent to 208.7 rupees and Sesa Goa lost 6.4 percent to 203.8
rupees.  KS Oils Ltd. (KSO)  , a manufacturer and processor of
edible oils, fell 4.5 percent to 9.55 rupees. The company’s
owners are in talks with  Ruchi Soya Industries Ltd. (RSI)   and
international firms such as Archer-Daniels-Midland Co. and
Cargill Inc. to sell a 35.01 percent stake, the Financial
Express reported without saying where it got the information.
Ruchi Soya sank 3.3 percent to 99 rupees.  Mphasis Ltd. (MPHL)  , an Indian software-maker, retreated
5.4 percent to 347.5 rupees after it was cut to “sell” from
“reduce” at Elara Securities India Pvt. The brokerage has a
share-price estimate of 360 rupees.  Reliance Capital Ltd. (RCAPT)   tumbled 12 percent to
344.2 rupees, its lowest since March 2009. The financial
services company controlled by billionaire  Anil Ambani  will be
removed in the Nifty from Oct. 10, replacing  Coal India Ltd. (COAL) 
. Coal India lost 4.1 percent to 359.4 rupees.  Reliance Industries Ltd. (RIL)   dropped 4.5 percent to
719.4 rupees, its lowest in 29 months. The company, controlled
by billionaire  Mukesh Ambani  will probably miss a target of
drilling 11 new wells at India’s biggest natural gas deposit by
March 31, a person with direct knowledge of the matter said.  Tree House Education & Accessories Ltd. (THEAL IN) declined
13 percent to 117.6 in its trading debut. The operator of pre-
schools in Mumbai raised 1.12 billion rupees ($24 million)
selling 8.43 million shares at 135 rupees apiece in an initial
public offer. Retail investors received a discount of 6 rupees
per share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
